TITLE: Defining OAuth2RequestError class extending Error in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet details a class that extends the built-in Error class to represent errors returned from OAuth 2.0 providers. It captures specific properties associated with OAuth 2.0 error responses, enabling structured error handling and easier debugging in OAuth-related workflows.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pilcrowonpaper/arctic/blob/main/docs/pages/reference/main/OAuth2RequestError.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
interface Properties {
	code: string;
	description: string | null;
	uri: string | null;
	state: string | null;
}

// Represents an OAuth 2.0 error response, extending the Error class
class OAuth2RequestError extends Error {
	public properties: Properties;

	constructor(properties: Properties, message?: string) {
		super(message || `OAuth2 Error: ${properties.code}`);
		this.name = "OAuth2RequestError";
		this.properties = properties;
	}
}
```

